  "texts": [
    "Measures of classifiers' predictive accuracy, such as ROC-AUC, sensitivity and specificity vary depending upon the characteristics of the targeted population (for example, according to prevalence and the proportion of COVID + and COVID -individuals that are symptomatic).",
    "Where possible, apply the classifier in a test set that reflects the appropriate application setting, for example, by subsampling a test set that is representative of the general population, as we do here. 6.",
    "Examine classifiers' expected utility.",
    "We can specify utilities for each testing outcome, that is, quantify the average benefit accrued from a true positive, the different benefit of a true negative, and similarly the costs attached to false positives and false negatives.",
    "Then the expected utility provides a highly context-specific score for quantifying and comparing classifiers' performance. 7."
